JASPER.name: Jasper
JASPER.tagline: Accelerating content creation with AI purpose-built for marketing teams and brand storytelling
JASPER.overview: Jasper (formerly Jarvis) is a generative AI platform for marketing content, founded in 2021 by Dave Rogenmoser, John Philip Morgan, and Chris Hull. The company raised $125M Series A in October 2022 at $1.5B valuation led by Insight Partners. Jasper was an early GPT-3 wrapper that grew rapidly to $120M revenue in 2023 but faced challenges with ChatGPT competition. In September 2023, Timothy Young (ex-Dropbox President) became CEO. In February 2024, Jasper acquired Clipdrop (15M users) from Stability AI. The company is pivoting to enterprise marketing AI with focus on brand voice and campaign workflows.
